      <h2 style="font-family:'Helvetica Neue',serif;font-size:34px;color:#59595C;margin-bottom:16px;">Built for the way organisations work now.</h2>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:#59595C;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:14px;">Many organisations still use job evaluation methods designed for a more stable world — one with slower change, more fixed role boundaries, and heavier reliance on detailed job descriptions.</p>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:#59595C;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:14px;">In many modern organisations those approaches begin to struggle. Roles evolve faster than documentation. Structures become more fluid. Specialist, managerial, commercial, and project-based roles become harder to compare.</p>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:#59595C;line-height:1.8;">Engage responds to those realities — allowing organisations to evaluate roles through five structured judgement grids, with a stronger emphasis on direct role knowledge, transparency of logic, and internal ownership over time.</p>
    </div>
